  "title": "The Peter Pan Cometh",
  "description": "Hook, Tinker, and Smee all dreamed of a life outside of their Neverland. Then along came Peter. From those who brought 2024's \"Who's Afraid of Winnie the Pooh?\"; it's The Ice Man Cometh, but Peter Pan. \"Clever, smart, ridiculous, and well executed\" - Cherry &amp; Spoon. \"Another triumph for the company\" - The Stages of MN.",
  "credits": "<strong>Director</strong>: Alexander Gerchak<br><strong>Cast</strong>: Alec Berchem; Thomas Buan; Nick Hill; Isabelle Hopewell<br/><strong>Designers</strong>: Genevieve Kafka; Connor McEvoy<br/><strong>Stage Manager</strong>: Karina Hunt<br/></br>",
  "website": "https://instagram.com/clevernametheatre",
  "plain_language": "The Peter Pan Cometh is about the pirate Captain Hook, his first mate Smee, and the faerie Tinkerbell, who are visited by their friend Peter Pan. When Peter Pan visits, he tells the others that he has grown up, and will help them grow up too. However, as time passes it becomes clear that things might not be what they seem.",
